From Bill Mayhew Subject Re help How to reduce the RPMs of a Boxer fan Yes you increase the RPM slip of a boxer type fan by installing a capacitor in series with the fan's power The air flow of small inch fans can be reduced by about by using a to uF Use a good grade nonpolarized unit with working voltage rating around Note that some impriical study is usually required to experimentally determine the best size capacitor for a given For DC powered applications try the Radio Shack volt box It can run and start reliably from as low as about It is exceptionally quiet but at admittedly low I wish I knew who made the fans for Radio Bill Mayhew NEOUCOM Computer Services Department Rootstown OH USA phone